<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Removal - Glow Plug Sleeve
        Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.2.11" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeve Removal</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>In-chassis removal of glow plug sleeves is only practical on the front two cylinders.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, if replacing glow plug sleeves in chassis, put a small plug in the
                    bottom of the glow plug sleeve before cutting threads. The plug will prevent small metal chips from
                    entering the combustion chamber.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>Glow plug sleeve removal is not required unless sleeves are damaged. If sleeve replacement is
                    required, see Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing in this section.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650442" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0850.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow plug sleeve remover (Thread tap)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate Glow Plug Sleeve Remover (thread tap) .</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The glow plug sleeve is made of stainless steel. Lubricate the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover
                        (thread tap) to get the threads started - otherwise excessive force would be necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650443" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08182.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow plug sleeve tapped</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut threads in the glow plug sleeve - at least 1/2 inch deep for the Glow Plug Sleeve
                Remover (bolt and sleeve adapter) .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650444" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08183.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow Plug Sleeve Remover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover into glow plug sleeve .</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650445" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08184.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removal of glow plug sleeve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a wrench to turn the bolt of the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover until the glow plug sleeve is
                extracted.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650446" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08185.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow plug sleeve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove glow plug sleeve.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
